{
  "text": "At small strain conditions, particle motion resulting from propagation of shear waves is nondestructive. As \u03b3 increases, the shear modulus will decrease from the maximum small strain value, G 0 . In-situ test have commonly been assumed to be small strain and the measurement of V s will be directly related to the G0 [CITATION_1] . The appropriate strain must be known, as well as the appropriate modulus reduction with increasing strain.",
  "citation_candidates": [
